---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import CalEmbed from '../components/CalEmbed.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import { SITE_DESCRIPTION, SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
import { batches } from '../data/batches';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <BaseHead title={SITE_TITLE} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />
    <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
      '@context': 'https://schema.org',
      '@graph': [
        {
          '@type': 'Organization',
          '@id': 'https://yarova.ca/#org',
          name: 'Yarova',
          url: 'https://yarova.ca',
          email: 'hello@yarova.ca',
          address: { '@type': 'PostalAddress', addressLocality: 'Langley', addressRegion: 'BC', addressCountry: 'CA' },
          foundingDate: '2018',
        },
        {
          '@type': 'Service',
          '@id': 'https://yarova.ca/#program',
          name: 'Yarova — Real Canadian DevOps & SRE Production Experience',
          serviceType: 'Structured 8-week remote workplace simulation for IT professionals',
          provider: { '@id': 'https://yarova.ca/#org' },
          areaServed: { '@type': 'Country', name: 'Canada' },
          offers: { '@type': 'Offer', price: '2400', priceCurrency: 'CAD' },
        },
      ],
    })} />
  </head>
  <body>
    <a class="skip" href="#main">Skip to content</a>
    <Header />

    <main id="main">

      <!-- 1 · HERO -->
      <section class="hero">
        <div class="container">
          <h1>Get Real Canadian DevOps or SRE Production Experience in 8 Weeks.</h1>
          <p class="sub">A structured remote workplace simulation for IT professionals. Join a squad of 4, report to a veteran Team Lead, and ship real code to real AWS infrastructure. We provide full career support from resume rewrites through clearing your 90-day job probation.</p>
          <div class="actions">
            <a href="#enroll"
               class="btn btn-amber btn-lg">Book a 30-Min Enrollment Call <span class="arrow">&rarr;</span></a>
          </div>
          <p class="price-label"><b>$2,400 CAD Flat.</b> No hidden fees. No income-share traps.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- 2 · THE REALITY CHECK -->
      <section id="wall" class="section alt">
        <div class="container">
          <h2>Why your applications are hitting a wall.</h2>

          <div class="wall-grid">
            <div class="wall-block">
              <div class="wall-label">The Loop</div>
              <p>You need Canadian experience to get a job offer. But you need a job offer to get Canadian experience.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="wall-block">
              <div class="wall-label">The Problem</div>
              <p>Stacking basic certificates, watching tutorials, and building copy-paste portfolio projects no one asked for isn&rsquo;t working. Hiring managers spot these artificial profiles in 10 seconds.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="wall-block">
              <div class="wall-label">The Fix</div>
              <p>Your brain isn&rsquo;t broken. The system is. Yarova breaks the loop by giving you actual, verifiable engineering history.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- 3 · THE TWO OPERATIONAL TRACKS -->
      <section id="tracks" class="section">
        <div class="container">
          <h2>The two operational tracks.</h2>

          <div class="two-col">
            <div class="track-block">
              <h3>DevOps &amp; DevSecOps Track</h3>
              <dl>
                <dt>The Focus</dt>
                <dd>Build, automate, and secure CI/CD pipelines and infrastructure.</dd>
                <dt>What you build</dt>
                <dd>Infrastructure as Code (IaC) with Terraform, automated deployments, container security.</dd>
                <dt>The Tool Stack</dt>
                <dd class="tools">AWS &middot; Terraform &middot; GitHub Actions &middot; Kubernetes &middot; Docker</dd>
              </dl>
            </div>
            <div class="track-block">
              <h3>Site Reliability Engineering (SRE) Track</h3>
              <dl>
                <dt>The Focus</dt>
                <dd>Maintain system availability, performance, and uptime.</dd>
                <dt>What you build</dt>
                <dd>Production health monitoring, real-time incident drilling, alerting systems, runbooks.</dd>
                <dt>The Tool Stack</dt>
                <dd class="tools">AWS &middot; Kubernetes &middot; Prometheus &middot; Grafana &middot; PagerDuty</dd>
              </dl>
            </div>
          </div>

          <p class="bottom-line"><b>The Bottom Line:</b> Every single ticket you complete is a permanent commit under the Yarova GitHub organization. It is real code that hiring managers can audit.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- 4 · THE PREDICTABLE STRUCTURE -->
      <section id="day" class="section alt">
        <div class="container">
          <h2>A day at Yarova.</h2>

          <ol class="day-grid">
            <li><span class="t">09:00</span><span class="b"><b>Squad Standup:</b> 15 minutes on Zoom. State what you shipped, what is next, and your blockers.</span></li>
            <li><span class="t">09:30</span><span class="b"><b>Pull Your Ticket:</b> Get your scope and acceptance criteria directly from the Yarova board.</span></li>
            <li><span class="t">12:00</span><span class="b"><b>Lunch Break:</b> Standard, non-negotiable operational downtime.</span></li>
            <li><span class="t">13:00</span><span class="b"><b>Deep Engineering Work:</b> Write code, open PRs, and collaborate with your squad on Slack.</span></li>
            <li><span class="t">15:00</span><span class="b"><b>Peer Code Review:</b> Review your squadmates&rsquo; pull requests to understand alternative logic.</span></li>
            <li><span class="t">16:00</span><span class="b"><b>Team Lead Office Hours:</b> Drop-in support with your Senior Engineer to get unblocked.</span></li>
            <li><span class="t">17:00</span><span class="b"><b>Daily Update:</b> Post your final progress update to your squad channel and sign off.</span></li>
          </ol>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- 5 · THE POST-BATCH CAREER RUNWAY -->
      <section id="runway" class="section">
        <div class="container">
          <h2>The post-batch career runway.</h2>
          <p class="lead">After the 8 weeks of engineering work, the exact 5-step process that takes you from finishing the program to clearing 90-day probation in a real job.</p>

          <ol class="runway-list">
            <li>
              <span class="rn">01</span>
              <div class="rb">
                <h3>Ticket-Based Resume Reconstruction</h3>
                <p>We don&rsquo;t write what Yarova is &mdash; we document exactly what you shipped, bullet-by-bullet, using your real GitHub commits.</p>
              </div>
            </li>
            <li>
              <span class="rn">02</span>
              <div class="rb">
                <h3>Custom Interview Preparation</h3>
                <p>The moment you book an interview with a company, we meet to run mock interviews matching that specific company&rsquo;s technical format.</p>
              </div>
            </li>
            <li>
              <span class="rn">03</span>
              <div class="rb">
                <h3>Background Check Documentation</h3>
                <p>We walk you through how to properly document your time at Yarova so your application clears standard Canadian background screens with zero ambiguity.</p>
              </div>
            </li>
            <li>
              <span class="rn">04</span>
              <div class="rb">
                <h3>Day-One Briefing</h3>
                <p>Before your first day on the new job, we brief you on the environment, expectations, and pitfalls to avoid in week one.</p>
              </div>
            </li>
            <li>
              <span class="rn">05</span>
              <div class="rb">
                <h3>90-Day Probation Support</h3>
                <p>We check in at 30, 60, and 90 days to help you navigate production issues or team dynamics, ensuring you clear probation and stay stable.</p>
              </div>
            </li>
          </ol>

          <div class="runway-finish"><span class="check">&#10003;</span> <b>The Standard:</b> Probation cleared. That is the finish line.</div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- 6 · DIRECT TERMS & ENROLLMENT -->
      <section id="enroll" class="section alt">
        <div class="container">
          <h2>Direct terms &amp; enrollment.</h2>

          <h3 class="sub-h">Live batch schedule</h3>
          <div class="batches-wrap">
            <table class="batches">
              <thead>
                <tr>
                  <th scope="col">Start date</th>
                  <th scope="col">Track</th>
                  <th scope="col">Seats remaining</th>
                  <th scope="col" class="end"><span class="sr-only">Action</span></th>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody>
                {batches.map((b) => {
                  const full = b.seatsLeft === 0;
                  return (
                    <tr class={full ? 'full' : ''}>
                      <td><span class="date">{b.dayLabel}</span></td>
                      <td><span class={`pill pill-${b.track === 'DevOps' ? 'devops' : 'sre'}`}>{b.track}</span></td>
                      <td class="seats">
                        {full
                          ? <span class="seats-full">Full</span>
                          : <span>{b.seatsLeft} of {b.seatsTotal}</span>}
                      </td>
                      <td class="end">
                        {full
                          ? <span class="waitlist">Waitlist</span>
                          : <a class="btn btn-amber btn-sm" href="https://cal.com/yarova-fxqeea/discovery-call" target="_blank" rel="noopener" data-cal-link="yarova-fxqeea/discovery-call" data-cal-namespace="discovery-call" data-cal-config='{"layout":"month_view"}'>Book Call to Reserve <span class="arrow">&rarr;</span></a>}
                      </td>
                    </tr>
                  );
                })}
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>

          <h3 class="sub-h">The flat-rate terms</h3>
          <ul class="terms">
            <li><b>Price:</b> $2,400 CAD (One-time payment before Day 1). Interest-free 3-month split plan available upon request.</li>
            <li><b>The Safety Net:</b> If you complete your tickets but do not secure a placement, you join the very next batch completely free. You do not pay twice.</li>
            <li><b>The Exclusions:</b> We do not guarantee an employer partnership, we do not cover your personal cloud costs (~$50 total), and we do not assist candidates located outside of Canada.</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="sub-h">Final CTA &mdash; Book a 30-minute fit call</h3>
          <p class="lead-narrow">Pick a time below. No deposit. We confirm the right batch on the call.</p>
          <CalEmbed namespace="discovery-call" inline calLink="yarova-fxqeea/discovery-call" height="720px" />
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- 7 · FAQ (accordion at the bottom) -->
      <section id="faq" class="section">
        <div class="container narrow">
          <h2>FAQ.</h2>

          <div class="faq">
            <details>
              <summary><span>How to explain no Canadian experience in an IT interview?</span><span class="glyph">+</span></summary>
              <div class="answer"><p>You point to verifiable, time-stamped GitHub commits under the Yarova organization &mdash; real tickets you shipped against real acceptance criteria, reviewed by a senior Canadian engineer. &ldquo;No Canadian experience&rdquo; becomes &ldquo;8 weeks of structured Canadian engineering work, here is the repo, here is the reference.&rdquo;</p></div>
            </details>
            <details>
              <summary><span>Is this real work or a simulation that looks real?</span><span class="glyph">+</span></summary>
              <div class="answer"><p>The work is real. The repositories live under the Yarova GitHub organization. The infrastructure runs on real AWS accounts. The tickets have real acceptance criteria and real reviewers. The only thing &ldquo;simulated&rdquo; is the employer relationship &mdash; you are not on Yarova&rsquo;s payroll. Everything you ship is yours, on your GitHub, permanently.</p></div>
            </details>
            <details>
              <summary><span>Why only 4 seats per batch?</span><span class="glyph">+</span></summary>
              <div class="answer"><p>Because a Team Lead can run a real standup, review every PR personally, and hold a weekly 1:1 with four engineers. Not with twelve. Cap the squad at four and the program stays intense; lift the cap and it becomes a course.</p></div>
            </details>
            <details>
              <summary><span>Why multiple batches each month?</span><span class="glyph">+</span></summary>
              <div class="answer"><p>So you start when you are ready, not in three months. Some batches run 09:00&ndash;17:00 PT (the standard Canadian-tech-company shift); some run 13:00&ndash;21:00 PT (the evening shift, for engineers who still hold a day job during the program). Pick the one that fits your life.</p></div>
            </details>
            <details>
              <summary><span>Will my Yarova work pass a Canadian background check?</span><span class="glyph">+</span></summary>
              <div class="answer"><p>Yes. Yarova Inc. is a Canadian company registered in British Columbia. Your work is documented as a contract engagement with Yarova Inc. We provide the verification letter. We are listed as your reference. We pick up the phone when the background-check company calls.</p></div>
            </details>
            <details>
              <summary><span>I already have a job. Can I do this part-time?</span><span class="glyph">+</span></summary>
              <div class="answer"><p>Yes &mdash; pick the evening shift batch (13:00&ndash;21:00 PT). You attend an evening standup and do your ticket work after your day job. Several engineers have shipped real work this way; it is intense but it works.</p></div>
            </details>
            <details>
              <summary><span>Do you guarantee me a job?</span><span class="glyph">+</span></summary>
              <div class="answer"><p>No. Anyone who guarantees you a job is lying. What we guarantee: if you complete your tickets and do not secure a placement, you join the very next batch completely free, and we keep going until you do. You do not pay twice.</p></div>
            </details>
            <details>
              <summary><span>Why $2,400? Why not more, why not less?</span><span class="glyph">+</span></summary>
              <div class="answer"><p>Less and the Team Lead can&rsquo;t be paid fairly &mdash; and a Team Lead who is not paid fairly does not show up for the PR review. More and we are charging for prestige instead of work. $2,400 covers a real Team Lead&rsquo;s time for eight weeks, the AWS bill on the shared infra, and the post-batch interview-and-probation support &mdash; with no markup for branding.</p></div>
            </details>
            <details>
              <summary><span>What if I am not in Canada?</span><span class="glyph">+</span></summary>
              <div class="answer"><p>We only place into Canadian roles right now. We know that market &mdash; the employers, the comp bands, the interview formats, the background-check vendors. If you are not in Canada (or arriving within 6 months on a valid work authorization), we will say no on the discovery call. Honest no, free, no follow-up.</p></div>
            </details>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

    </main>

    <Footer />

    <!-- Floating actions -->
    <div class="floating-actions" aria-label="Quick contact">
      <a class="fa-btn wa" href="https://wa.me/16047197918?text=Hi%20Yarova%2C%20I%27d%20like%20to%20learn%20more." target="_blank" rel="noopener" aria-label="Message Yarova on WhatsApp">
        <span class="ic" aria-hidden="true"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor"><path d="M19.05 4.91A9.82 9.82 0 0 0 12.04 2c-5.46 0-9.91 4.45-9.91 9.91 0 1.75.46 3.46 1.32 4.96L2.05 22l5.25-1.38c1.45.79 3.08 1.21 4.74 1.21 5.46 0 9.91-4.45 9.91-9.91 0-2.65-1.03-5.14-2.9-7.01Zm-7.01 15.24c-1.48 0-2.94-.4-4.21-1.15l-.3-.18-3.12.82.83-3.04-.2-.31a8.26 8.26 0 0 1-1.26-4.38c0-4.54 3.7-8.24 8.24-8.24a8.18 8.18 0 0 1 8.24 8.24c.01 4.54-3.69 8.24-8.22 8.24Zm4.52-6.16c-.25-.12-1.47-.72-1.69-.81-.23-.08-.39-.12-.56.12s-.64.81-.78.97c-.14.17-.29.19-.54.06-.25-.12-1.05-.39-1.99-1.23-.74-.66-1.23-1.47-1.38-1.72-.14-.25-.02-.38.11-.51.11-.11.25-.29.37-.43.12-.14.16-.25.25-.41.08-.17.04-.31-.02-.43-.06-.12-.56-1.34-.76-1.84-.2-.48-.4-.42-.56-.43-.14-.01-.31-.01-.48-.01-.17 0-.43.06-.66.31-.23.25-.86.85-.86 2.07s.89 2.4 1.01 2.56c.12.17 1.75 2.67 4.23 3.74.59.26 1.05.41 1.41.52.59.19 1.13.16 1.56.1.48-.07 1.47-.6 1.67-1.18.21-.58.21-1.07.14-1.18-.05-.11-.21-.17-.45-.29Z"/></svg></span>
        <span class="lbl">WhatsApp</span>
      </a>
      <a class="fa-btn cal" href="#enroll" aria-label="Jump to enrollment">
        <span class="ic" aria-hidden="true"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.4" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><rect x="3" y="5" width="18" height="16" rx="2"/><path d="M16 3v4M8 3v4M3 10h18"/></svg></span>
        <span class="lbl">Book a call</span>
      </a>
    </div>

    <!-- FAQ glyph toggle -->
    <script>
      document.querySelectorAll('.faq details').forEach(function (d) {
        var g = d.querySelector('.glyph');
        if (g && d.open) g.textContent = '−';
        d.addEventListener('toggle', function () {
          if (g) g.textContent = d.open ? '−' : '+';
        });
      });
    </script>

    <style>
      * { box-sizing: border-box; }
      html { scroll-behavior: smooth; scroll-padding-top: 88px; }
      @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) { html { scroll-behavior: auto; } * { animation: none !important; transition: none !important; } }

      a { color: var(--color-amber-hover); text-decoration: none; }
      a:hover { color: var(--color-amber-press); }
      a:focus-visible { outline: none; box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px rgba(217,119,6,.28); border-radius: 4px; }
      .skip { position: absolute; left: -9999px; top: 8px; background: var(--color-black); color: white; padding: 10px 14px; border-radius: 8px; font-size: 14px; z-index: 999; }
      .skip:focus { left: 12px; }

      .container { max-width: 1080px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 32px; }
      .container.narrow { max-width: 760px; }
      .section { padding: 88px 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); }
      .section.alt { background: var(--bg-secondary); }

      h1, h2, h3 { font-family: var(--font-sans); margin: 0; color: var(--fg-1); letter-spacing: -.02em; }
      h1 { font-size: clamp(30px, 4.6vw, 52px); font-weight: 700; line-height: 1.15; letter-spacing: -.025em; max-width: 920px; }
      h2 { font-size: clamp(26px, 3.4vw, 38px); font-weight: 700; line-height: 1.2; margin-bottom: 32px; }
      h3 { font-size: 18px; font-weight: 600; line-height: 1.35; }
      p { margin: 0; color: var(--fg-2); line-height: 1.65; }
      .lead { font-size: 16px; color: var(--fg-2); max-width: 760px; margin: -16px 0 36px; }
      .lead-narrow { font-size: 15px; color: var(--fg-2); max-width: 540px; margin: -8px 0 24px; }

      /* Buttons */
      .btn { display: inline-flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; gap: 10px; padding: 14px 22px; border-radius: 8px; font-family: var(--font-sans); font-size: 15px; font-weight: 600; line-height: 1; border: 1px solid transparent; cursor: pointer; transition: transform 120ms ease, background 150ms; text-decoration: none; }
      .btn-sm { padding: 8px 14px; font-size: 13px; }
      .btn-lg { padding: 18px 28px; font-size: 16px; }
      .btn-amber { background: var(--color-amber-hover); color: white !important; }
      .btn-amber:hover { background: var(--color-amber-press); transform: translateY(-1px); }
      .btn .arrow { transition: transform 180ms ease; display: inline-block; }
      .btn:hover .arrow { transform: translateX(3px); }

      /* 1 · Hero */
      .hero { padding: 88px 0 72px; }
      .sub { font-size: 17px; color: var(--fg-2); margin-top: 24px; max-width: 720px; line-height: 1.6; }
      .actions { display: flex; gap: 14px; margin-top: 32px; flex-wrap: wrap; }
      .price-label { margin-top: 18px; font-size: 14px; color: var(--fg-2); }
      .price-label b { color: var(--fg-1); }

      /* 2 · Wall (catch-22) */
      .wall-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 20px; }
      .wall-block { background: var(--bg-primary); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 10px; padding: 24px; }
      .wall-label { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 11px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: .14em; color: var(--color-amber-hover); font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 12px; }
      .wall-block p { font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.6; }
      @media (max-width: 800px) { .wall-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }

      /* 3 · Tracks */
      .two-col { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 20px; }
      .track-block { background: var(--bg-secondary); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 10px; padding: 28px; }
      .track-block h3 { margin: 0 0 20px; }
      .track-block dl { margin: 0; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 14px; }
      .track-block dt { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 11px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: .14em; color: var(--color-amber-hover); font-weight: 600; }
      .track-block dd { margin: 4px 0 0; font-size: 14px; color: var(--fg-2); line-height: 1.6; }
      .track-block .tools { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 12px; color: var(--fg-1); letter-spacing: .04em; }
      .bottom-line { margin-top: 28px; padding: 18px 22px; background: var(--color-black); color: rgba(255,255,255,.85); border-radius: 8px; font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.6; }
      .bottom-line b { color: var(--color-amber); }
      @media (max-width: 760px) { .two-col { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }

      /* 4 · Day */
      .day-grid { list-style: none; margin: 0; padding: 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); }
      .day-grid li { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 90px 1fr; gap: 24px; padding: 16px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); align-items: baseline; }
      .day-grid .t { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 13px; color: var(--color-amber-hover); font-weight: 700; }
      .day-grid .b { font-size: 14px; color: var(--fg-2); line-height: 1.6; }
      .day-grid .b b { color: var(--fg-1); font-weight: 600; }
      @media (max-width: 600px) { .day-grid li { grid-template-columns: 70px 1fr; gap: 14px; } }

      /* 5 · Runway */
      .runway-list { list-style: none; margin: 0; padding: 0; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 12px; }
      .runway-list li { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 44px 1fr; gap: 18px; background: var(--bg-secondary); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 8px; padding: 20px 22px; align-items: start; }
      .runway-list .rn { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 13px; color: var(--color-amber-hover); font-weight: 700; padding-top: 2px; }
      .runway-list .rb h3 { font-size: 15px; margin-bottom: 6px; }
      .runway-list .rb p { font-size: 14px; color: var(--fg-2); line-height: 1.6; }
      .runway-finish { margin-top: 24px; padding: 18px 22px; background: var(--color-black); color: white; border-radius: 8px; font-size: 15px; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 12px; }
      .runway-finish .check { color: var(--color-amber); font-weight: 700; font-size: 18px; }
      .runway-finish b { color: var(--color-amber); font-weight: 600; }
      @media (max-width: 600px) { .runway-list li { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } .runway-list .rn { padding: 0; } }

      /* 6 · Enrollment */
      .sub-h { font-size: 13px !important; font-family: var(--font-mono) !important; text-transform: uppercase !important; letter-spacing: .14em !important; color: var(--color-amber-hover) !important; font-weight: 700 !important; margin: 40px 0 16px !important; }
      .sub-h:first-of-type { margin-top: 0 !important; }

      .batches-wrap { overflow-x: auto; border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 10px; background: var(--bg-primary); }
      .batches { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 14px; }
      .batches thead th { background: var(--bg-secondary); padding: 14px 16px; text-align: left; font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 11px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: .14em; color: var(--fg-3); font-weight: 600; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }
      .batches tbody td { padding: 16px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); vertical-align: middle; color: var(--fg-2); }
      .batches tbody tr:last-child td { border-bottom: none; }
      .batches tbody tr.full td { background: var(--bg-secondary); color: var(--fg-3); }
      .batches .date { font-weight: 600; color: var(--fg-1); }
      .batches .pill { display: inline-flex; align-items: center; padding: 4px 10px; border-radius: 999px; font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 11px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: .08em; font-weight: 700; }
      .batches .pill-devops { background: rgba(217,119,6,.12); color: var(--color-amber-hover); }
      .batches .pill-sre { background: rgba(13,148,136,.14); color: var(--color-teal-hover); }
      .batches .seats { font-weight: 600; color: var(--fg-1); }
      .batches .seats-full { color: var(--fg-3); }
      .batches .waitlist { font-size: 13px; color: var(--fg-3); font-style: italic; }
      .batches .end { text-align: right; white-space: nowrap; }

      .terms { list-style: none; margin: 0; padding: 0; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 14px; }
      .terms li { padding: 18px 22px; background: var(--bg-primary); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 8px; font-size: 14px; color: var(--fg-2); line-height: 1.65; }
      .terms b { color: var(--fg-1); font-weight: 600; }

      /* 7 · FAQ */
      .faq { border-top: 1px solid var(--border); }
      .faq details { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }
      .faq summary { padding: 20px 0; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; gap: 16px; cursor: pointer; list-style: none; min-height: 44px; }
      .faq summary::-webkit-details-marker { display: none; }
      .faq summary > span:first-child { font-size: 15px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--fg-1); line-height: 1.4; }
      .faq summary .glyph { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 22px; color: var(--color-amber-hover); font-weight: 400; flex-shrink: 0; }
      .faq .answer { padding: 0 0 20px; }
      .faq .answer p { font-size: 14px; color: var(--fg-2); line-height: 1.7; margin: 0 0 10px; }
      .faq .answer p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }

      /* Floating actions */
      .floating-actions { position: fixed; bottom: 20px; right: 18px; z-index: 55; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 8px; }
      .fa-btn { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 10px; padding: 10px 16px; border-radius: 999px; font-size: 13px; font-weight: 600; color: white !important; text-decoration: none; transition: transform 120ms ease; box-shadow: 0 8px 22px -8px rgba(0,0,0,.35); }
      .fa-btn:hover { transform: translateY(-2px); }
      .fa-btn.wa { background: #25D366; }
      .fa-btn.cal { background: var(--color-black); }
      .fa-btn .ic { width: 16px; height: 16px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; }
      .fa-btn .ic svg { width: 16px; height: 16px; }
      @media (max-width: 640px) { .fa-btn .lbl { display: none; } .fa-btn { padding: 12px; } }
    </style>
  </body>
